k for most cases is<br />to just create a patched kernel that fakes the lengths to some random value.<br />I've used this once to debug a kernel problem over NFS. Sick, but potentially<br />useful (I made all /proc files be 4096 bytes in length, which happens to be a<br />nice round random number). <br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
